data.enText: to make yourself/sb familiar with sth or become used to it

data.chText: 他过了一段时间才习惯这个想法。
data.enText: It took him a while to accustom himself to the idea.

simple_means.memory_skill: ac 加强 + custom 习惯 → 使习惯

ex.chText: 提前3天到达以适应新环境。
ex.enText: Arrive three days early so as to acclimatize.

ex.chText: 他习惯了寒冷之后，身体马上就好了。
ex.enText: He was fine once he had acclimatized himself to the cold.

ex.chText: 我们现已习惯上海炎热的夏天。
ex.enText: We're now acclimatized to the hot summers of Shanghai.

synonyms.bx: 指习惯新地方、新情况、新气候等。

tips.tip: 美国英语中常用 acclimate 一词表示此义。

ex.chText: 一个乡下人难以适应城市生活。
ex.enText: It is hard for a rural person to accustom himself to city life.

ex.chText: 他难以习惯寒冷的天气。
ex.enText: He can't accustom himself to the cold weather.

ex.chText: 我很快习惯了这份烦人的工作。
ex.enText: I soon got used to the tiresome job.
She has got used to country life.

ex.chText: 我习惯了苏格兰的天气。
ex.enText: I'm used to the weather in Scotland.

synonyms.bx: 也可说 be used to。用 get 时侧重于动作，用 be 时侧重于状态。

data.enText: to make yourself/sb familiar with sth or become used to it

data.chText: 他过了一段时间才习惯这个想法。
data.enText: It took him a while to accustom himself to the idea.

tr: make psychologically or physically used (to something)
example: She became habituated to the background music

value.def: If you accustom yourself or another person to something, you make yourself or them become used to it.

example.ex: The team has accustomed itself to the pace of first division rugby...
example.tran: 球队适应了英式橄榄球甲级联赛的节奏。

example.ex: Shakespeare has accustomed us to a mixture of humor and tragedy in the same play.
example.tran: 莎士比亚让我们习见了同一场戏目中的悲喜交错。

partsOfSpeech.dec: ac 加强 + custom 习惯 → 使习惯
custom 习惯 + ary …的 → 习惯性的
custom 习惯 + er 表名词 → 习惯〔进商店的〕人 → 顾客
